\left(x+\frac1x\right)^{100} = \sum_{k=0}^{100} {100\choose k} x^{k}\frac{1}{x^{100-k}} = \sum_{k=0}^{100} {100\choose k} x^{k}x^{k-100} = \sum_{k=0}^{100} {100\choose k} x^{2k-100}.
k
2k-100 = 50
